title: Football DE - Bundesliga 2

creator: XOOPsoft
descriptionHtml:
Standings
The standings screen is updated live as matches are being played. You can see team rank changes illustrated by up or down arrows. You can also use the checkbox at the top to see the standings before current matches started.
When you tap on a team in the standings table, you can find extended standings information. You can also see the latest matches played by the team.

Live score
Here you will find the matches closest to the current date. On the "misc" tab you can find cup matches, and more.
Tap on a match and see all the details about who scored, substitutions, yellow and red cards.
You can use the filter button if you only want to see some of the details.
On the statistics page you can see ball possession, shots, fouls, and more.
The line-up page shows you the start formation with players on field and players/coach on the bench.

Schedule
Here you find all the matches of the current season - fixtures and results. The matches are group by round. Use the arrows to page back and forth between rounds.

Top scorer / Statistics
Here you can find the top scorer list, yellow cards list, red cards list, penalty list, and more.

Team
Use the popup menu and choose a team. Then you can see all matches grouped by team. Again, you can tap on each match to find all the details.

Settings
Here you have several options. For example: Choose your notification details level. Choose teams to be notified about. Choose app text size. Choose app theme color.
You can get push notifications about lineup, match start, goals, red cards, cancelled goals, and more.

Support for Android Wear with live score notifications.

The app has also the option to remove all ads for a small amount.
With the same subscription you will also get the current match scores directly in the live score notifications.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml:
A new and more unified design.
Easier to find the functionality of each page with the new navigation chips at the top.

In the app settings you can choose your preferred textsize for the whole app.

Extended standings with home/away information. Latest matches of each team. Stadium information. You can find the new popup when you tap on a team in the standings.

Matches are grouped per day.
